title._content: James Fitzpatrick of 'Travelogue' fame onboard CARONIA

description._content:
Black and white photograph, landscape format, head and shoulder portrait of James Fitzpatrick. On the reverse of the print is the handwritten inscription: `James Fitzpatrick of "Travelogue fame" onboard RMS CARONIA Feb 1951.'

James Fitzpatrick was an American documentary film maker who specialised in travel documentaries. He visited Australian shores in early 1951. During the three days RMS CARONIA was in Sydney in February 1951 Fitzpatrick filmed the sites and attractions of the city.


The ANMM undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. 

Photographer: Henry Gawthorpe
